The repository link for this project is <https://github.com/ideolo/image-super-resolution>. You can download the latest version of the code from this link.

Alternatively, you can install the package using pip by running the following command:
```
pip install ISR
```
Once you have installed the package, you can use the `RDN` model to perform super-resolution on images. Here is an example of how to do this:
```
from ISR.models import RDN

# Load the pre-trained RDN model
rdn = RDN(weights='psnr-small')

# Load the low-resolution image
lr_img = Image.open('data/input/test_images/sample_image.jpg')

# Convert the image to a numpy array
lr_img = np.array(lr_img)

# Perform super-resolution on the image
sr_img = rdn.predict(lr_img)

# Display the super-resolved image
Image.fromarray(sr_img)
```
I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.</s>
